about the job
description

we are currently seeking a seasoned project manager for a contract position with our customer's engit group. engit is an internal, centralized technology group that supports the engineering organization (group that creates products for them). the support scm (source code management) tools. this pm will need to have worked in a devops environment in the past and ideally been exposed to scm tools such as git and bitbucket.

one example of why they exist: they do this work so engineers/developers do not have to worry about where code is stored or put builds into jenkins – they make it seamless for engineers to spin up a pipeline from a ui interface button and spin it up.

role description

the engineering devops as a service team that is looking for an experienced technical project manager. edaas is a fast-paced group that is working to modernize and evolve development workflows in their engineering with modern, cloud-native tools and processes. the ideal candidate is self-motivated to gather, manage and analyze data and processes to proactively support multiple service teams including containerized distribution, binary management, build management, source code management, etc.

responsibilities of this role
this role will provide leadership, technical direction, and guidance to a development team to design, implement, maintain, and update edaas projects as they relate to binary management, build management and source code management.
shall serve as the main point of contact to receive and collaborate on all work for the containerized distribution platform, collaborating with smes to ensure accuracy.
track project status across available tools enabling stakeholders to make decisions by communicating status, timelines, expectations, actions, risks, and next steps.
coordinate between a multitude of cross-functional teams and set clear expectations about responsibilities to internal customers.
understand the solution and implementation path to execute large, complex security and cloud programs.
you will work alongside engineers and various product teams in building secure integration across our applications.
create roadmaps and drive execution.
provide weekly leadership updates.

skills and experience
5 years of experience in technical project management with practical expertise in process analysis, change management, risk management and communications.
experience working with engineering and leadership teams (e.g., engineering managers, product managers, security engineers, site reliability engineers, software engineers, and developer operations.)
experience in open-source technologies and/or cloud infrastructure and saas environment.
experience on a devops team and is familiar with scm and ci/cd concepts.
domain experience in one or more of the following:
basic python or bash scripting, saml sso, scim, okta, github actions, etc.
exercise design and architecture related knowledge to develop and drive technical solutions alongside development teams.
working knowledge of jenkins, artifactory, github, aws, and sonarqube.
be comfortable in a fast-paced, self-guided, dynamic, and innovative environment.
demonstrate a willingness to be flexible and adaptable to changing priorities.
agile working environment utilizing jira cloud.
pmp certification a plus.

here are the engit offerings to the various teams they support in their engineering organization.

artifactory: scalable artifact management with a tightly-coupled integration to jenkins.

devhub: an external artifactory binary repository management solution for their external users.

dockerhub: secure, cisco-hosted, and geographically distributed registry for docker container images built on jfrog artifactory.

git lfs: a secure, cisco-hosted large file storage service which helps you to separate your large binary files and your source code.

jenkins - centralized: multi-tenant, enterprise jenkins from cloudbees software providing continuous integration to global teams, enabling repeatable build management and monitoring of job execution. shared instance with shared build nodes to get your team adopting continuous integration immediately.

jenkins - dedicated: jenkins enterprise installed for an individual team to use. provides administrative access to the development team and is supported and managed 24x7x365 by the engit ci team.

selenium box: allows you to simulate different browser sessions for testing web applications.

sonarqube: an open source static analysis tool used for gathering code quality metrics.

must work est hours.
